Project description

Documentation

Full documentation and additional training examples are available onhttp://www.comet.com/docs/

Installation

  • Sign up (free) on comet.com and obtain an API key at https://www.comet.com

Getting started: 30 seconds to Comet.ml

The core class of Comet.ml is an Experiment, a specific run of ascript that generated a result such as training a model on a single setof hyper parameters. An Experiment will automatically log scripts output (stdout/stderr), code, and commandline arguments on any script and for the supported libraries willalso log hyper parameters, metrics and model configuration.

Here is the Experiment object:

from comet_ml import Experimentexperiment = Experiment(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")# Your code.

We all strive to be data driven and yet every day valuable experimentsresults are just lost and forgotten. Comet.ml provides a dead simple wayof fixing that. Works with any workflow, any ML task, any machine andany piece of code.

For a more in-depth tutorial about Comet.ml, you can check out or docs http:/www.comet.com/docs/
